ased","1314":"1314","1345":"1345","about 1290":"about 1290","before 1320":"before 1320","1230":"1230","1285":"1285","1262":"1262","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Monmouthshire, Wales":"Monmouthshire, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Llewellyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: from the personal name <i>Llywelyn</i>, derived from British Celtic <i>Lugubelinos</i>, itself from the divine name <i>Lugus</i> + an uncertain second element often used alone as a name. Through association with <i>llew</i> ‘lion’, it was altered to <i>Llewelyn</i>. This was the name of two princes of north Wales who held the Normans at bay for many years in the 13th century. Etymologically speaking, the form with a fourth <i>-l-</i> is an error, not found as an original Welsh name, but this is now much the most common spelling in the US."],"variants":[{"name":"Lewelling","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Llewellyn  ."]},{"name":"Lewellen","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Llewellyn  ."]},{"name":"Lewallen","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Llewellyn  ."]},{"name":"Louallen","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh <b>Llewelyn</b> (see   Llewellyn  )."]},{"name":"Luellen","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Llewellyn  ."]},{"name":"Welling","meanings":["English: habitational name from Welwyn (Hertfordshire) or Welling in Bexley (Kent), with a suspicion of an alternative unidentified source. The Hertfordshire placename means ‘at the willow trees’, from Old English <i>wel(i)gum</i>, dative plural form of <i>welig</i> ‘willow’. The Kent placename may derive from Old English <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’ + the placename forming suffix <i>-ing</i>. In some cases this name may represent a development of   Llewellyn  , particularly near the Welsh border.","German: habitational name from any of various places in the Rhineland called Welling or Wellingen."]},{"name":"Luallen","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Llewellyn  ."]},{"name":"Lewellyn","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Llewellyn  ."]},{"name":"Llewelyn","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Llewellyn  ."]}]},{"name":"Verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lleneu Verch Llewellyn was born about 1290, in Wales as the daughter of Llewellyn ap Owen and Mrs Llewellyn ap Owen."},"et":{"about 1290–":"umbes 1290–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1314–Female":"1314–Surnud","1345–1370":"1345–1370","1262–Male":"1262–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1314":"1314","1345":"1345","about 1290":"umbes 1290","before 1320":"enne 1320","1230":"1230","1285":"1285","1262":"1262","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Monmouthshire, Wales":"Monmouthshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1290–":"noin 1290–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1314–Female":"1314–Kuollut","1345–1370":"1345–1370","1262–Male":"1262–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1314":"1314","1345":"1345","about 1290":"noin 1290","before 1320":"ennen vuotta 1320","1230":"1230","1285":"1285","1262":"1262","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Cardiganshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales","Monmouthshire, Wales":"Monmouthshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1290–":"environ 1290–Décédée","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1285–Male